name: Maine

processing_metadata.description: Official Maine DMV processing rules and validation requirements

global_rules.code_system: Maine uses code numbers to identify plate types
global_rules.character_restrictions: Do not make new plates using letter O or I because they are easily confused with numbers 0 and 1. If someone already had plates with those letters, they have been allowed to keep them.; Full rules: Do not make new plates using the letter O or I because they are so easily confused with the numbers 0 and 1. If someone already had plates with those letters, they have allowed them to keep them.
global_rules.processing_note: Processing rules vary by plate type and are defined in the CSV matrix. Custom processing types will be provided separately.
global_rules.no_prefix_suffix: Maine does not have a prefix or suffix system. Duplicated plates can only be identified by plate type (class of plate).
global_rules.no_duplication_new_plates: Maine does not allow duplication on new vanity plates or specialty plates to prevent further duplication.
global_rules.letter_restrictions: Do not make new plates using letter O or I because they are easily confused with numbers 0 and 1. Existing plates with these letters are grandfathered.
global_rules.emergency_vehicle_rule: Reject images of Marked Emergency Vehicles for codes 61 and 67
global_rules.omit_stacked_rule: Omit stacked characters: COM (31), BUS (64), TLR (71)

stacked_characters.position: Y - Do NOT key verticals.; Y - Vertical BUS is not verified; Y- Key all verticals
